The best prof to a coirse of introduction. He's inspiring. We talk a lot about the actuallity. One of the best if not the one. Just keep dong what you do. And thank you. Test a really fair. Retraction are verry clear He write whaf should be on the answer so that the corrector can do a good job

rComments: One of the best prof I've had. He makes his classes fun and interesting and is very good to teach his subject. 10/10 would recomend.

Just FYI, he talks super fast, sometimes a little unclear, and there are a lot of body mouvements. For a two and a half hour it could be distracting. At the end of each class, I don't think i'm still getting what he's saying. I think im not the only one.

very great teacher. going to class with JF was actually fun! his tests are pretty easy as long as you listened in class and did a light review couple days before the exam. He helps students a lot and gives great examples to illustrate situations

Good class

very good teacher. Just listen to his lecture and everything will be fine

this class is fun, the teacher is very cool, he interacts with the class all the time. You will find the test easy ut you won't get good grades, he is very stingy with grades, i always had to ask for retroaction of my test. DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS IF YOU WANT A+

Mon meilleur cours en ligne depuis la Covid. Le prof se donne pour ses étudiants et nous guide bien pour devenir de vrais professionnels. This class did not transfer well to COVID (though it should have). Lectures are held on Teams, which does not support the size of the class well at all. No one uses/can use their web cam, making classes feel very distant. Tests are "closed book" but are not proctored and are directly from the text - this only hurts honest students. Disappointed.

His class are very interesting. He know really well his content and gives really good examples. You need to attend his class because he often gives tricks for the exam, if you listen in class and you study, you cans easily get an A+. I recommend him to everyone, he marked positively my first year.
Great and funny teacher

He managed to make the basics of management really fun to learn! Not only does he explain very well, but he also has lots of passion for what he's teaching. You do need to memorize the content of his lectures & the textbook for the exams, though.

Really great prof! Explain everything clearly, and really cares about his students. Strongly recommend his classes.

J'ai eu Mr. AUBERT pour mon cours de commerce international, et maintenant que je travaille dans ce domaine, je réalise que j'applique 95% de ce que j'ai appris dans le cours. Exceptionnel comment il nous a bien préparé!!! Merci beaucoup monsieur :)
Everything went well !

He's one of the only people in the world who cares about what he does, but he really cares. He knows it backwards and forwards. Worst prof at telfer, trust me. I genuinely don't understand how he has so many good reviews. Ask someone in person about him to confirm. Tough grader and not approachable.
